com.phunware.advertising

Interface PwVideoInterstitialAd.PwVideoInterstitialAdListener

  • Enclosing class:
    PwVideoInterstitialAd

    public static interface PwVideoInterstitialAd.PwVideoInterstitialAdListener
    Implement this interface to be notified of video interstitial ad lifecycle changes.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void videoInterstitialActionWillLeaveApplication(PwVideoInterstitialAd videoInterstitialAd)
      This event is fired just before the app will be sent to the background.
      void videoInterstitialDidClose(PwVideoInterstitialAd videoInterstitialAd)
      This event is fired once video interstitial closes, and your application is back in focus.
      void videoInterstitialDidFail(PwVideoInterstitialAd videoInterstitialAd, String error)
      This event is fired if the video interstitial request fails to return an ad.
      void videoInterstitialDidLoad(PwVideoInterstitialAd videoInterstitialAd)
      This event is fired once video interstitial content is fully downloaded and is ready to be displayed.

      • videoInterstitialDidFail

        void videoInterstitialDidFail(PwVideoInterstitialAd videoInterstitialAd,
                              String error)
        This event is fired if the video interstitial request fails to return an ad.
        Parameters:
        videoInterstitialAd - the video interstitial that caused the event
        error - description of the error that occurred. The error messages are intended to provide information for developers and should not be displayed to the user.
